================================================================================
GAMEPLAY DEPTH — OOTP-Tier Features
================================================================================
Features that would bring the game to a competitive level with top sports sims.

NARRATIVE & STAKES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Owner Goals / Season Expectations — owner sets win targets, budget compliance,
  and development mandates each season. Missing targets affects job security and
  future flexibility. Creates urgency beyond just winning the championship.

Team Chemistry / Locker Room System — team-level morale modifier on top of
  individual player morale. Winning streaks boost it, losing streaks tank it,
  star players leaving damages it. Affects sim ratings for the entire roster.

Player Personality Archetypes — leadership, work ethic, and coachability
  ratings per player beyond dev trait. Affects development speed, locker room
  health, and contract negotiation behavior. Ties into coaching and morale.

Player Retirement Control — players announce retirement intentions before the
  offseason ends. User can attempt to convince them to return for one more year
  with a contract offer. Currently auto-retirement with no player input.

ROSTER / PLAYER MANAGEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Injury History / Injury-Prone Trait — track career injury history per player.
  Players with repeated injuries accumulate an injury-prone flag that increases
  in-game injury probability and lowers market value. Builds on existing injury
  system.

Scouting Department — hire scouts with regional specialties that improve
  draft prospect accuracy over time. Builds directly on the existing combine
  measurables and 25-point scouting system.

SIMULATION & SCHEDULE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Realistic Schedule Generation — division-based scheduling with proper
  home/away splits and divisional game weighting. Current schedule is fully
  random, making standings feel arbitrary.

Multi-Season Batch Simulation — "Sim N seasons" with a progress bar. Critical
  for dynasty feel — users should be able to fast-forward through rebuilds.

LEAGUE & FINANCIALS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Franchise & League Records — best single-season and career performances by
  team (franchise records) and across the entire league (all-time records).
  Requires adding team_id to career_stats_history (migration) and a records
  query layer. Data is already preserved — this is purely a UI + query build.
  Examples: Packers single-season passing yards record, all-time league sacks
  leader, team rushing TD record holder.

Financial System Beyond Cap — market size per team affecting revenue, stadium
  attendance, and owner budget. Even a simplified version (large market vs.
  small market affecting cap floor and FA appeal) adds a meaningful meta layer.

Commissioner / Full Control Mode — control all 32 teams, edit any roster, and
  simulate full seasons hands-free. Standard in sports sims at this level.

