MAINTENANCE — Address before extended dynasty saves become common
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[DONE June 20, 2026] Startup Migration Check Consolidation — all PRAGMA
  table_info column checks removed from initDatabase(). Consolidated into
  versioned migration v8. CURRENT_SCHEMA_VERSION bumped to 8.

[DONE June 20, 2026] News Events Archiving — DELETE fired on every season
  advance in advanceSeason(). Keeps last 3 seasons in news_events, prunes
  everything older. Uses existing idx_news_season_week index.

Raw Stats Table Pruning — the stats table (individual game rows) grows at
  ~170K rows/season and is the largest table in the save file. career_stats_history
  already archives all per-season aggregates at season-end, so raw stats rows
  older than 2 seasons can be safely deleted after archival. Implement as an
  additional DELETE in advanceSeason() after the career_stats_history INSERT:
    DELETE FROM stats WHERE season < current - 1
  This keeps the current and prior season for in-app stat lookups while
  preventing multi-season saves from bloating.

career_stats_history team_id Column — currently stores player stats per season
  with no team context. Needed before Franchise Records can be built. Requires:
  1. Migration to add team_id INTEGER to career_stats_history.
  2. Update the season-end INSERT in advanceSeason() to populate team_id by
     joining through the stats table (stats → games is not needed; players.team_id
     at time of archival is sufficient for most cases).
  Prerequisite for the Franchise & League Records feature above.

